7 EVALUATION :
7-1:Our adaptive duty cycling algorithm was evaluated using an actual solar energy profile measured using a sensor node called Heliomote, capable of harvesting solar energy [14] .
7-2:This platform not only tracks the generated energy but also the energy flow into and out of the battery to provide an accurate estimate of the stored energy .
7-3:The energy harvesting platform was deployed in a residential area in Los Angeles from the beginning of June through the middle of August for a total of 72 days .
7-4:The sensor node used is a Mica2 mote running at a fixed 40% duty cycle with an initially full battery .
7-5:Battery voltage and net current from the solar panels are sampled at a period of 10 seconds .
7-6:The energy generation profile for that duration, measured by tracking the output current from the solar cell is shown in Figure 4, both on continuous and diurnal scales .
7-7:We can observe that although the energy profile varies from day to day, it still exhibits a general pattern over several days .
