8 CONCLUSIONS :
8-1:We discussed various issues in power management for systems powered using environmentally harvested energy .
8-2:Specifically, we designed a method for optimizing performance subject to the constraint of energy neutral operation .
8-3:We also derived a theoretically optimal bound on the performance and showed that our proposed algorithm operated very close to the optimal .
8-4:The proposals were evaluated using real data collected using an energy harvesting sensor node deployed in an outdoor environment .
8-5:Our method has significant advantages over currently used methods which are based on a conservative estimate of duty cycle and can only provide sub optimal performance .
8-6:However, this work is only the first step towards optimal solutions for energy neutral operation .
8-7:It is designed for a specific power scaling method based on adapting the duty cycle .
8-8:Several other power scaling methods, such as DVS, submodule power switching and the use of multiple low power modes are also available .
8-9:It is thus of interest to extend our methods to exploit these advanced capabilities. .
